snippet.title: Ed Sheeran - Sapphire (Official Music Video)
snippet.description:
Listen to 'Sapphire' now: https://es.lnk.to/sapphireID

"Sapphire was the first song I finished for Play that made me know where the album was heading. It's why I finished the recording process in Goa surrounded by some of the best musicians in India. It was an incredible creative process. I shot the music video with Liam Pethick and Nic Minns across my India tour earlier this year, we wanted to showcase the beauty and breadth of the country and its culture. The final jigsaw piece for me was getting @Official_ArijitSingh on the record, but it was a journey to get there and such an amazing day of music and family. Me and him have done a full Punjabi version of the song that will come out in the next few weeks, which has a lot more of him on it. This is the album version of the song, and my favourite song on the album. Hope you guys love it. Sapphire out now" - Ed x

Pre-order 'Play' out September 12: https://es.lnk.to/playID

We bring to you the best videos from your favorite show Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah. So, get your daily dose of laughter with Jethalal, Taarak Mehta, Daya, Champaklal and their neighbors in Gokuldham Society.

About Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah:
--------------------------------------------------------------------
The show is inspired from the famous humorous column 'Duniya Ne Undha Chasma' written by the eminent Gujarati writer Mr. Tarak Mehta. This story revolves around daily happenings in "Gokuldham Co-operative Society" and covers topical issues which are socially relevant. The show predominantly - revolves around 'Jethalal' who is an uneducated Gujarati businessman. Your 'Taarak Mehta', is his neighbor. 'Jethalal' finds a friend and philosopher in 'Taarak Mehta' and often goes to him for advice whenever he is in trouble. Jethalaal's family includes his simpleton wife 'Daya Ben' and a mischievous son 'Tapu'. Tapu is a menace and a constant source of trouble to all the members of Gokuldham. They have often warned 'Jethalal' to reform 'Tapu' or else be prepared to leave the premises. Lost hopes of being heard by his son push Jethalal' to call his father 'Champaklal' from the village. This was his great idea of leashing some control over the mischievous Tapu. The opposite happens and the grandfather joins hands with the grandson to make life a roller coaster troublesome ride for Jethalal.

Dilip Joshi as Jethalal Champaklal Gada

We bring to you the best videos from your favorite show Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah. So, get your daily dose of laughter with Jethalal, Taarak Mehta, Daya, Champaklal and their neighbors in Gokuldham Society.

About Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah:
--------------------------------------------------------------------
The show is inspired from the famous humorous column 'Duniya Ne Undha Chasma' written by the eminent Gujarati writer Mr. Tarak Mehta. This story revolves around daily happenings in "Gokuldham Co-operative Society" and covers topical issues which are socially relevant. The show predominantly - revolves around 'Jethalal' who is an uneducated Gujarati businessman. Your 'Taarak Mehta', is his neighbor. 'Jethalal' finds a friend and philosopher in 'Taarak Mehta' and often goes to him for advice whenever he is in trouble. Jethalaal's family includes his simpleton wife 'Daya Ben' and a mischievous son 'Tapu'. Tapu is a menace and a constant source of trouble to all the members of Gokuldham. They have often warned 'Jethalal' to reform 'Tapu' or else be prepared to leave the premises. Lost hopes of being heard by his son push Jethalal' to call his father 'Champaklal' from the village. This was his great idea of leashing some control over the mischievous Tapu. The opposite happens and the grandfather joins hands with the grandson to make life a roller coaster troublesome ride for Jethalal.

snippet.title: Ronth| Official Trailer| Dileesh Pothan, Roshan Mathew| Directed by Shahi Kabir| In Cinemas 13 June
snippet.description:
A gripping cop drama which follows a stoic senior police officer haunted by his past and his idealistic young partner assigned to night patrols. Their clashing personalities ignite tension, but as a series of intense and emotional events unfold, a reluctant bond begins to form. When a life-threatening incident threatens their careers, both must confront their deepest fears and darkest truths to survive the shadows of duty.


Genre - Drama 

#Ronth #RonthInCinemas13thJune #ShahiKabir #DileeshPothan #RoshanMathew #JungleePictures #FestivalCinemas 


Starring - Dileesh Pothan, Roshan Mathew, Sudhi Koppa, Arun Cherukavil, Krisha Kurup, Nandanunni, Lakshmi Menon and Baby Nandhootty

About the show: 
----------------------------------------------------------------------
Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah is a SAB Comedy Show inspired by the famous humorous column, Duniya Ne Undha Chashmah written by the eminent Gujarati writer, Mr. Tarak Mehta. This show revolves around the Gada family which consists of businessman, Jethalal Champaklal Gada, Jethalal's wife, Daya & their naughty son, Tipendra Gada living in Gokuldham Co-operative Society, and covers topical issues that are socially relevant. This hilarious show will surely tickle your funny bone.

snippet.title: Forgotten Malayalam Movies S06 E01 | Radio | Malayalam Movie Review Funny | Thalaivasal VJ
snippet.description:
Forgotten Malayalam Movies is a movie review series where we review some of the greatest (read : worst) movies in malayalam.

This season's first movie is Radio. Radio was released on Mother's day 2013 and was a knockout blockbuster, destroying all its competitors by a huge margin. Radio was the inspiration for a number of movies like Paa (Bollywood) and The Curious Case Of Benjamin Button (Hollywood). It is said that Brad Pitt personally called Thalaivasal VJ and thanked him being an inspiration. One of the best films that you can watch with your mother, Radio will definitely go down in history as one of  the greatest feel good family movies of all time!

snippet.description:

I hope you enjoy it and really excited to see how all of you feel towards the next parts that are coming out :)

snippet.description:

https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLPbh-P_C0BzRYOkpGxKL-6QmvYSL_ZuCu

We bring to you the best videos from your favorite show Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah. So, get your daily dose of laughter with Jethalal, Taarak Mehta, Daya, Champaklal and their neighbors in Gokuldham Society.

About Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah:
--------------------------------------------------------------------
The show is inspired from the famous humorous column 'Duniya Ne Undha Chasma' written by the eminent Gujarati writer Mr. Tarak Mehta. This story revolves around daily happenings in "Gokuldham Co-operative Society" and covers topical issues which are socially relevant. The show predominantly - revolves around 'Jethalal' who is an uneducated Gujarati businessman. Your 'Taarak Mehta', is his neighbor. 'Jethalal' finds a friend and philosopher in 'Taarak Mehta' and often goes to him for advice whenever he is in trouble. Jethalaal's family includes his simpleton wife 'Daya Ben' and a mischievous son 'Tapu'. Tapu is a menace and a constant source of trouble to all the members of Gokuldham. They have often warned 'Jethalal' to reform 'Tapu' or else be prepared to leave the premises. Lost hopes of being heard by his son push Jethalal' to call his father 'Champaklal' from the village. This was his great idea of leashing some control over the mischievous Tapu. The opposite happens and the grandfather joins hands with the grandson to make life a roller coaster troublesome ride for Jethalal.

Cast:
---------
Dilip Joshi as Jethalal Champaklal Gada
Disha Vakani as Daya Jethalal Gada
Nitish Bhaluni / Raj Anadkat / Bhavya Gandhi as Tipendra Jethalal Gada (Tapu)

Gurucharan Singh/ Balwinder Suri as Roshan Singh Harjeet Singh Sodhi

Witness the heartwarming story of brotherhood and family values in "Om Jai Jagadish." Released in 2002, this Hindi film beautifully portrays the lives of three brothers and their unwavering bond despite facing various trials and tribulations. When their father passes away, the eldest brother, Om, selflessly takes on the responsibility of caring for his younger siblings, Jai and Jagadish. As they navigate life's challenges, including financial difficulties and personal aspirations, their unity is tested. Will their strong familial love withstand the pressures of the outside world? Experience a captivating narrative filled with emotion, drama, and memorable performances from a stellar cast.

Welcome to our deep-dive analysis of Housefull 5 Box Office Collection Worldwide! In this video, we break down the Housefull 5 Total Collection across both domestic and international markets. From the much-hyped Housefull 5 1st Day Collection to its overall performance, we‚Äôve got all the numbers to show how this star-packed comedy thriller is faring globally.

Directed by Tarun Mansukhani and produced by Sajid Nadiadwala under Nadiadwala Grandson Entertainment, Housefull 5 features a massive ensemble: Akshay Kumar, Riteish Deshmukh, Abhishek Bachchan, Sanjay Dutt, Jacqueline Fernandez, Nargis Fakhri, and more. With a reported Housefull 5 Movie Budget of around ‚Çπ375 crores, it‚Äôs among the biggest Bollywood comedies ever made.

But is it living up to the hype? Our Housefull 5 Movie Review explores the film‚Äôs comedy, chaos, and star power. We‚Äôll also look at whether Housefull 5 can break franchise records and become a blockbuster of 2025.

From grand visuals to a suspense-filled cruise setting, this video covers:
- Housefull 5 India & overseas collections
- Housefull 5 Budget vs. earnings

- Housefull 5 Public reactions & critic reviews

We bring to you the best videos from your favorite show Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah. So, get your daily dose of laughter with Jethalal, Taarak Mehta, Daya, Champaklal and their neighbors in Gokuldham Society.

About Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah:
--------------------------------------------------------------------
The show is inspired from the famous humorous column 'Duniya Ne Undha Chasma' written by the eminent Gujarati writer Mr. Tarak Mehta. This story revolves around daily happenings in "Gokuldham Co-operative Society" and covers topical issues which are socially relevant. The show predominantly - revolves around 'Jethalal' who is an uneducated Gujarati businessman. Your 'Taarak Mehta', is his neighbor. 'Jethalal' finds a friend and philosopher in 'Taarak Mehta' and often goes to him for advice whenever he is in trouble. Jethalaal's family includes his simpleton wife 'Daya Ben' and a mischievous son 'Tapu'. Tapu is a menace and a constant source of trouble to all the members of Gokuldham. They have often warned 'Jethalal' to reform 'Tapu' or else be prepared to leave the premises. Lost hopes of being heard by his son push Jethalal' to call his father 'Champaklal' from the village. This was his great idea of leashing some control over the mischievous Tapu. The opposite happens and the grandfather joins hands with the grandson to make life a roller coaster troublesome ride for Jethalal.

snippet.title: BANANA BAJJI | Banana Fry | Valakkai Bajji Recipe  Cooking in Village | Tasty Plantain Evening Snack
snippet.description:
Today in our village, we made a delicious and crispy Banana Bajji using raw plantains, also known as Valakkai Bajji in Tamil. This traditional South Indian snack, especially in Kerala and Tamil Nadu, is a perfect evening treat, especially when served hot with tea. We sliced fresh plantains, dipped them in a flavorful gram flour batter seasoned with spices, and deep-fried them over a woodfire stove until golden and crisp.

Our village-style cooking brings out the authentic taste and aroma of this simple yet tasty snack. Watch how we prepare these bajjis in a natural outdoor setting, using fresh ingredients and traditional methods.

Enjoy the satisfying crunch and soft banana filling in every bite! Perfect for family gatherings or as a festive snack.
tags: how to make banana bajji at home

La nostra cucina in stile villaggio esalta il gusto e l'aroma autentici di questo spuntino semplice ma gustoso. Guarda come prepariamo questi bajji in un ambiente naturale all'aperto, utilizzando ingredienti freschi e metodi tradizionali.

Hari ini di desa kami, kami membuat Bajji Pisang yang lezat dan renyah menggunakan pisang mentah, yang juga dikenal sebagai Valakkai Bajji dalam bahasa Tamil. Camilan tradisional India Selatan ini, khususnya di Kerala dan Tamil Nadu, merupakan sajian malam yang sempurna, terutama jika disajikan hangat dengan teh. Kami mengiris pisang segar, mencelupkannya ke dalam adonan tepung gram yang beraroma dan dibumbui dengan rempah-rempah, dan menggorengnya di atas tungku kayu bakar hingga berwarna keemasan dan renyah.

Cara memasak ala desa kami menghasilkan rasa dan aroma asli dari camilan sederhana namun lezat ini. Saksikan cara kami menyiapkan bajji ini di alam terbuka, menggunakan bahan-bahan segar dan metode tradisional.

Nikmati kerenyahan yang memuaskan dan isian pisang yang lembut di setiap gigitan! Sempurna untuk acara kumpul keluarga atau sebagai camilan hari raya.

snippet.title: Tata Harrier EV AWD First Impressions | Gagan Choudhary
snippet.description:
Tata Motors finally launched their first AWD SUV in the last 5 years, Harrier.ev. It is an electric SUV that comes with Dual Motor. Tata Motors call it QWD or Qual Wheel drive. Harrier Electric will also come with RWD single motor setup as standard. The starting price of the Harrier electric 65 kWh RWD base variant is Rs 21.49 Lakh Ex-Showroom. The other battery pack is 75 kWh. This car can do 0-100 in just 6.3 seconds in Dual motor AWD trim and should give a practical range of up to 480 km in RWD single motor variant.

snippet.title: The greatest chess finish ever | Gukesh vs Magnus Carlsen | Norway Chess 2025
snippet.description:
World no.1 Magnus Carlsen and World Champion D. Gukesh clashed against each other in round 1 of Norway Chess and that game ended in Magnus' favour. We are now back for the 2nd game in the tournament, this time Gukesh has the white pieces against the Norwegian legend. Would Gukesh be able to get his revenge, or will Magnus show his class once again! Check out this amazing game along with IM Sagar Shah's commentary and enjoy the greatest chess finish that you can ever expect.
